# pyc float64 str() shows full %.17g precision (1234567.8899999999) instead
# of CPython's shortest round-trip repr (1234567.89) for values without an
# exact binary representation -- pre-existing, already-documented gap (see
# tests/str_builtin_call.py.python.expect_fail), not introduced by the
# ifa/if1/num.cc sprint_float_val fix that stopped this specific value from
# being silently corrupted to 1234570.0 in generated C code.
